# Certo Website Clone – Responsive Front-End Project

Technologies: HTML5, CSS3, Vanilla JavaScript  
Volume: 24,295 lines of code (HTML: 3,855 | CSS: 18,015 | JS: 2,425)  
Responsive: Yes (breakpoints: 1024px, 768px, 480px, 360px)  
Developer: Frontend Developer from Belarus

A fully responsive front-end clone of the official Certo security software website. This educational project focuses on complex layouts, cross-device compatibility, and front-end development techniques. Certo provides tools for detecting spyware, stalkerware, and other security threats on mobile devices. This clone replicates its core design and user interface for learning purposes.

## Features
   Full Responsiveness: Adapts to all major screen sizes (Desktop, Laptop, Tablet, Mobile)
   Complete Page Set: 10 unique pages cloned (homepage, product pages, blog, support)
   CSS Animations: Custom animations (about 10 different animations) built using CSS @keyframes
   Interactive Components: Functional navigation, modals, accordions with vanilla JavaScript
   Clean Code: Well-structured semantic HTML5 and modular CSS

